 It was so sad. &#10;In the third the girl was at Uni and had a minor breakdown. Drank heavily, weed and a fair few boys. Nothing serious long term but she'd had her life controlled for so long up to that point with the freedom she went a bit bonkers. &#10;These cases may not be a fair or quantitive sample but they are my interaction with home schooling is wholly negative and I tend to think that it is cruel to the children and basically practiced by parents who have massive egos and are a bit bonkers. It should be banned. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="810" language="en" documentId="1071" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="calminthestorm" date="28 July 2010 10:32pm" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://discussion.theguardian.com/comment-permalink/6870231" topic="homeschooling" thumbsUp="9" thumbsDown="0" origId="1071" notes="" title="Home education: precious, not dangerous"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="41"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="42" end="166"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="47" sofa="1" begin="167" end="305"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="51" sofa="1" begin="306" end="537"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="55" sofa="1" begin="538" end="810"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43 47 51 55"/></xmi:XMI>